Sec. 149.006. INJUNCTION. On a conviction of an offense under
this chapter, the court shall enjoin the defendant from slaughtering
Statute text rendered on: 8/6/2022

- 860 -

AGRICULTURE CODE

animals, selling meat, transporting meat, or in any manner purveying
meat to the public as food for human consumption. Each day the
injunction is violated constitutes a separate contempt.
Added by Acts 1991, 72nd Leg., ch. 16, Sec. 2.01(a), eff. Aug. 26,
1991.

